article.headline: Washington 67, Oregon 56
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Giuliana Mendiola scored 18 points in the
second half as Washington defeated Oregon 67-56 on Saturday.

Mendiola led the Huskies with 22 points. She was 6-for-9 from
the field in the second half and connected on five three-pointers.

Mendiola scored 18 of Washington's final 23 points and paced the
Huskies with nine rebounds.

Andrea Lalum scored 16 points and had eight rebounds for the
Huskies, who have won their last four games over the Ducks. The win
gives Washington (14-10, 7-8) two in a row at McArthur Court after
losing nine straight in Eugene.

Brandi Davis was 3-of-8 from beyond the three-point line and led
the Ducks with 19 points. Andrea Bills had her 18th double-double
of the season, posting 10 points and 10 rebounds.

Oregon (12-12, 4-10) tied the game at 27 two minutes into the
second half, but the Huskies went on a 9-0 run over the next two
and a half minutes to break the game open.

The Ducks got within two at the 8:29 mark, but no closer.
Washington took a 25-23 lead into halftime after a sloppily played
first half. The teams combined to shoot just 30 percent from the
field.
